			<Description>Ritual Site</Description>
			<Civilopedia>Use of incense in religion is prevalent in many cultures and may have their roots in the practical and aesthetic uses considering that many religions with not much else in common all use incense. One common motif is incense as a form of sacrificial offering to a deity. Such religious ceremonies often take place at a religious site such as a shrine.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Tobacco had already long been used in the Americas, with some cultivation sites in Mexico dating back to 1400â€“1000 B.C. Eastern North American tribes carried large amounts of tobacco in pouches as a readily accepted trade item, and often smoked it in peace pipes, either in defined sacred ceremonies, or to seal a bargain.</Civilopedia>
			<Strategy>The Ritual Site can only be constructed in a city with improved incense or tobacco resources nearby. The Ritual Site increases the [ICON_CULTURE] Culture and [ICON_PEACE] Faith output of each such resource the city has access to. Military Land Units trained in the City may heal faster (+10 HP per turn).</Strategy>
			<Help>Each source of [ICON_RES_INCENSE] Incense and [ICON_RES_TOBACCO] Tobacco worked by this City produces +1 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture and +1 [ICON_PEACE] Faith. Military Land Units trained in this City may heal faster.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]City must have at least one of these resources worked nearby.</Help>
